paper_metadata.title: MAIN TEXT
paper_metadata.extraction_summary: The paper discusses variants in the TTR gene associated with transthyretin amyloid cardiomyopathy, specifically T60A and V122I, along with penetrance data.

functional_data.summary: The T60A variant is associated with hereditary amyloidosis.

variants.additional_notes: The variant is more prevalent in females compared to wild-type.
key_quotes: Female prevalence was greater in T60A-hATTR-CM (29.6%) compared to wtATTR-CM (6%).

functional_data.summary: The V122I variant is associated with hereditary amyloidosis.

variants.additional_notes: The variant is associated with a higher mortality rate in males.
key_quotes: In the V122I-hATTR-CM group, 61 (50.8%) of the 120 females died compared to 177 (56.9%) of the 311 males.

extraction_metadata.notes: All relevant data regarding TTR variants were extracted from the main text.
